WorkItem.Description:
Consider this case:

```
myFunction(len: number) {
    var len: number = 5;     // re-definition of local variable (name clash)
}
```

I understand that EcmaScript allows local variables to be redefined, so it's not an option to flag this as an error in TypeScript.

It would however be great if the TypeScript compiler just generates a warning for such a case.

Another case would be:

```
myFunction() {
    var b: number = a;       // variable a is accessed before it is declared/initialized
    var a: number = 5;
}
```

This is a consequence of variable hoisting in EcmaScript. Here too, a warning would be great.
